obo:BFO_0000050  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_905  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper studies the distribution of NKAα1 and NKAα3 in the rat spiral ganglion and in the organ of Corti\n\nFigure 3D-E demonstrates membrane staining for NKAα3 directly surrounding cytoplasmatic Neurofilament 200, an intermediate filament enriched in the cytoplasm of both types I and II spiral ganglion somata and processes. NKAα3 immunoreactivity is localized to the cell membranes and bouton-shaped endings of the NF200-expressing type I afferent terminals. These staining support a postsynaptic membrane localization of the NKAα3.\n\n19/8/2017 Pim\n- Localization to the plasma membrane not annotated because not shown in the experimental data.. Experimental description: Whole cochleae were dissected from rats and immediately perfused through the round window with 4% paraformaldehyde (PFA) in phosphate-buffered saline (PBS) at pH 7.4." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_905" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

